12106
12107/* Generate GOMP_cancel call for #pragma omp cancel. */
12108
12109void
12110c_finish_omp_cancel (location_t loc, tree clauses)
12111{
12112 tree fn = builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_GOMP_CANCEL);
12113 int mask = 0;
12114 if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_PARALLEL))
12115 mask = 1;
12116 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_FOR))
12117 mask = 2;
12118 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_SECTIONS))
12119 mask = 4;
12120 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_TASKGROUP))
12121 mask = 8;
12122 else
12123 {
12124 error_at (loc, "%<#pragma omp cancel%> must specify one of "
12125 "%<parallel%>, %<for%>, %<sections%> or %<taskgroup%> "
12126 "clauses");
12127 return;
12128 }
12129 tree ifc = omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_IF);
12130 if (ifc != NULL_TREE)
12131 {
12132 tree type = TREE_TYPE (OMP_CLAUSE_IF_EXPR (ifc));
12133 ifc = fold_build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (ifc), NE_EXPR,
12134 boolean_type_node, OMP_CLAUSE_IF_EXPR (ifc),
12135 build_zero_cst (type));
12136 }
12137 else
12138 ifc = boolean_true_node;
12139 tree stmt = build_call_expr_loc (loc, fn, 2,
12140 build_int_cst (integer_type_node, mask),
12141 ifc);
12142 add_stmt (stmt);
12143}
12144
12145/* Generate GOMP_cancellation_point call for
12146 #pragma omp cancellation point. */
12147
12148void
12149c_finish_omp_cancellation_point (location_t loc, tree clauses)
12150{
12151 tree fn = builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_GOMP_CANCELLATION_POINT);
12152 int mask = 0;
12153 if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_PARALLEL))
12154 mask = 1;
12155 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_FOR))
12156 mask = 2;
12157 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_SECTIONS))
12158 mask = 4;
12159 else if (omp_find_clause (clauses, OMP_CLAUSE_TASKGROUP))
12160 mask = 8;
12161 else
12162 {
12163 error_at (loc, "%<#pragma omp cancellation point%> must specify one of "
12164 "%<parallel%>, %<for%>, %<sections%> or %<taskgroup%> "
12165 "clauses");
12166 return;
12167 }
12168 tree stmt = build_call_expr_loc (loc, fn, 1,
12169 build_int_cst (integer_type_node, mask));
12170 add_stmt (stmt);
12171}
12172
12173/* Helper function for handle_omp_array_sections. Called recursively
12174 to handle multiple array-section-subscripts. C is the clause,
12175 T current expression (initially OMP_CLAUSE_DECL), which is either
12176 a TREE_LIST for array-section-subscript (TREE_PURPOSE is low-bound
12177 expression if specified, TREE_VALUE length expression if specified,
12178 TREE_CHAIN is what it has been specified after, or some decl.
12179 TYPES vector is populated with array section types, MAYBE_ZERO_LEN
12180 set to true if any of the array-section-subscript could have length
12181 of zero (explicit or implicit), FIRST_NON_ONE is the index of the
12182 first array-section-subscript which is known not to have length
12183 of one. Given say:
12184 map(a[:b][2:1][:c][:2][:d][e:f][2:5])
12185 FIRST_NON_ONE will be 3, array-section-subscript [:b], [2:1] and [:c]
12186 all are or may have length of 1, array-section-subscript [:2] is the
12187 first one known not to have length 1. For array-section-subscript
12188 <= FIRST_NON_ONE we diagnose non-contiguous arrays if low bound isn't
12189 0 or length isn't the array domain max + 1, for > FIRST_NON_ONE we
12190 can if MAYBE_ZERO_LEN is false. MAYBE_ZERO_LEN will be true in the above
12191 case though, as some lengths could be zero. */
12192
12193static tree
12194handle_omp_array_sections_1 (tree c, tree t, vec<tree> &types,
12195 bool &maybe_zero_len, unsigned int &first_non_one,
12196 enum c_omp_region_type ort)
12197{
12198 tree ret, low_bound, length, type;
12199 if (TREE_CODE (t) != TREE_LIST)
12200 {
12201 if (error_operand_p (t))
12202 return error_mark_node;
12203 ret = t;
12204 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12205 && TYPE_ATOMIC (strip_array_types (TREE_TYPE (t))))
12206 {
12207 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), "%<_Atomic%> %qE in %qs clause",
12208 t, omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12209 return error_mark_node;
12210 }
12211 if (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF
12212 && ort == C_ORT_OMP
12213 && (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_MAP
12214 || OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_TO
12215 || OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_FROM))
12216 {
12217 if (DECL_BIT_FIELD (TREE_OPERAND (t, 1)))
12218 {
12219 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12220 "bit-field %qE in %qs clause",
12221 t, omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12222 return error_mark_node;
12223 }
12224 while (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF)
12225 {
12226 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0))) == UNION_TYPE)
12227 {
12228 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12229 "%qE is a member of a union", t);
12230 return error_mark_node;
12231 }
12232 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
12233 }
12234 }
12235 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
12236 {
12237 if (DECL_P (t))
12238 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12239 "%qD is not a variable in %qs clause", t,
12240 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12241 else
12242 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12243 "%qE is not a variable in %qs clause", t,
12244 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12245 return error_mark_node;
12246 }
12247 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12248 && TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t)))
12249 {
12250 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), "%<_Atomic%> %qD in %qs clause",
12251 t, omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12252 return error_mark_node;
12253 }
12254 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12255 && VAR_P (t)
12256 && DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (t))
12257 {
12258 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12259 "%qD is threadprivate variable in %qs clause", t,
12260 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12261 return error_mark_node;
12262 }
12263 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12264 && TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t))
12265 && POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (t)))
12266 {
12267 /* If the array section is pointer based and the pointer
12268 itself is _Atomic qualified, we need to atomically load
12269 the pointer. */
12270 c_expr expr;
12271 memset (&expr, 0, sizeof (expr));
12272 expr.value = ret;
12273 expr = convert_lvalue_to_rvalue (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12274 expr, false, false);
12275 ret = expr.value;
12276 }
12277 return ret;
12278 }
12279
12280 ret = handle_omp_array_sections_1 (c, TREE_CHAIN (t), types,
12281 maybe_zero_len, first_non_one, ort);
12282 if (ret == error_mark_node || ret == NULL_TREE)
12283 return ret;
12284
12285 type = TREE_TYPE (ret);
12286 low_bound = TREE_PURPOSE (t);
12287 length = TREE_VALUE (t);
12288
12289 if (low_bound == error_mark_node || length == error_mark_node)
12290 return error_mark_node;
12291
12292 if (low_bound && !INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (low_bound)))
12293 {
12294 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12295 "low bound %qE of array section does not have integral type",
12296 low_bound);
12297 return error_mark_node;
12298 }
12299 if (length && !INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (length)))
12300 {
12301 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12302 "length %qE of array section does not have integral type",
12303 length);
12304 return error_mark_node;
12305 }
12306 if (low_bound
12307 && TREE_CODE (low_bound) == INTEGER_CST
12308 && TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (low_bound))
12309 > TYPE_PRECISION (sizetype))
12310 low_bound = fold_convert (sizetype, low_bound);
12311 if (length
12312 && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST
12313 && TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (length))
12314 > TYPE_PRECISION (sizetype))
12315 length = fold_convert (sizetype, length);
12316 if (low_bound == NULL_TREE)
12317 low_bound = integer_zero_node;
12318
12319 if (length != NULL_TREE)
12320 {
12321 if (!integer_nonzerop (length))
12322 {
12323 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12324 || OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12325 {
12326 if (integer_zerop (length))
12327 {
12328 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12329 "zero length array section in %qs clause",
12330 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12331 return error_mark_node;
12332 }
12333 }
12334 else
12335 maybe_zero_len = true;
12336 }
12337 if (first_non_one == types.length ()
12338 && (TREE_CODE (length) != INTEGER_CST || integer_onep (length)))
12339 first_non_one++;
12340 }
12341 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12342 {
12343 if (length == NULL_TREE
12344 && (TYPE_DOMAIN (type) == NULL_TREE
12345 || TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)) == NULL_TREE))
12346 {
12347 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12348 "for unknown bound array type length expression must "
12349 "be specified");
12350 return error_mark_node;
12351 }
12352 if (TREE_CODE (low_bound) == INTEGER_CST
12353 && tree_int_cst_sgn (low_bound) == -1)
12354 {
12355 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12356 "negative low bound in array section in %qs clause",
12357 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12358 return error_mark_node;
12359 }
12360 if (length != NULL_TREE
12361 && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST
12362 && tree_int_cst_sgn (length) == -1)
12363 {
12364 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12365 "negative length in array section in %qs clause",
12366 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12367 return error_mark_node;
12368 }
12369 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)
12370 && TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
12371 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)))
12372 == INTEGER_CST)
12373 {
12374 tree size
12375 = fold_convert (sizetype, TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)));
12376 size = size_binop (PLUS_EXPR, size, size_one_node);
12377 if (TREE_CODE (low_bound) == INTEGER_CST)
12378 {
12379 if (tree_int_cst_lt (size, low_bound))
12380 {
12381 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12382 "low bound %qE above array section size "
12383 "in %qs clause", low_bound,
12384 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12385 return error_mark_node;
12386 }
12387 if (tree_int_cst_equal (size, low_bound))
12388 {
12389 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12390 || OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12391 {
12392 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12393 "zero length array section in %qs clause",
12394 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12395 return error_mark_node;
12396 }
12397 maybe_zero_len = true;
12398 }
12399 else if (length == NULL_TREE
12400 && first_non_one == types.length ()
12401 && tree_int_cst_equal
12402 (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)),
12403 low_bound))
12404 first_non_one++;
12405 }
12406 else if (length == NULL_TREE)
12407 {
12408 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12409 && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12410 maybe_zero_len = true;
12411 if (first_non_one == types.length ())
12412 first_non_one++;
12413 }
12414 if (length && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST)
12415 {
12416 if (tree_int_cst_lt (size, length))
12417 {
12418 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12419 "length %qE above array section size "
12420 "in %qs clause", length,
12421 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12422 return error_mark_node;
12423 }
12424 if (TREE_CODE (low_bound) == INTEGER_CST)
12425 {
12426 tree lbpluslen
12427 = size_binop (PLUS_EXPR,
12428 fold_convert (sizetype, low_bound),
12429 fold_convert (sizetype, length));
12430 if (TREE_CODE (lbpluslen) == INTEGER_CST
12431 && tree_int_cst_lt (size, lbpluslen))
12432 {
12433 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12434 "high bound %qE above array section size "
12435 "in %qs clause", lbpluslen,
12436 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12437 return error_mark_node;
12438 }
12439 }
12440 }
12441 }
12442 else if (length == NULL_TREE)
12443 {
12444 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12445 && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12446 maybe_zero_len = true;
12447 if (first_non_one == types.length ())
12448 first_non_one++;
12449 }
12450
12451 /* For [lb:] we will need to evaluate lb more than once. */
12452 if (length == NULL_TREE && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND)
12453 {
12454 tree lb = c_save_expr (low_bound);
12455 if (lb != low_bound)
12456 {
12457 TREE_PURPOSE (t) = lb;
12458 low_bound = lb;
12459 }
12460 }
12461 }
12462 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == POINTER_TYPE)
12463 {
12464 if (length == NULL_TREE)
12465 {
12466 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12467 "for pointer type length expression must be specified");
12468 return error_mark_node;
12469 }
12470 if (length != NULL_TREE
12471 && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST
12472 && tree_int_cst_sgn (length) == -1)
12473 {
12474 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12475 "negative length in array section in %qs clause",
12476 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12477 return error_mark_node;
12478 }
12479 /* If there is a pointer type anywhere but in the very first
12480 array-section-subscript, the array section can't be contiguous. */
12481 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND
12482 && TREE_CODE (TREE_CHAIN (t)) == TREE_LIST)
12483 {
12484 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12485 "array section is not contiguous in %qs clause",
12486 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12487 return error_mark_node;
12488 }
12489 }
12490 else
12491 {
12492 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12493 "%qE does not have pointer or array type", ret);
12494 return error_mark_node;
12495 }
12496 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND)
12497 types.safe_push (TREE_TYPE (ret));
12498 /* We will need to evaluate lb more than once. */
12499 tree lb = c_save_expr (low_bound);
12500 if (lb != low_bound)
12501 {
12502 TREE_PURPOSE (t) = lb;
12503 low_bound = lb;
12504 }
12505 ret = build_array_ref (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), ret, low_bound);
12506 return ret;
12507}
12508
12509/* Handle array sections for clause C. */
12510
12511static bool
12512handle_omp_array_sections (tree c, enum c_omp_region_type ort)
12513{
12514 bool maybe_zero_len = false;
12515 unsigned int first_non_one = 0;
12516 auto_vec<tree, 10> types;
12517 tree first = handle_omp_array_sections_1 (c, OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c), types,
12518 maybe_zero_len, first_non_one,
12519 ort);
12520 if (first == error_mark_node)
12521 return true;
12522 if (first == NULL_TREE)
12523 return false;
12524 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND)
12525 {
12526 tree t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
12527 tree tem = NULL_TREE;
12528 /* Need to evaluate side effects in the length expressions
12529 if any. */
12530 while (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST)
12531 {
12532 if (TREE_VALUE (t) && TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (TREE_VALUE (t)))
12533 {
12534 if (tem == NULL_TREE)
12535 tem = TREE_VALUE (t);
12536 else
12537 tem = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (tem),
12538 TREE_VALUE (t), tem);
12539 }
12540 t = TREE_CHAIN (t);
12541 }
12542 if (tem)
12543 first = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (first), tem, first);
12544 first = c_fully_fold (first, false, NULL);
12545 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c) = first;
12546 }
12547 else
12548 {
12549 unsigned int num = types.length (), i;
12550 tree t, side_effects = NULL_TREE, size = NULL_TREE;
12551 tree condition = NULL_TREE;
12552
12553 if (int_size_in_bytes (TREE_TYPE (first)) <= 0)
12554 maybe_zero_len = true;
12555
12556 for (i = num, t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c); i > 0;
12557 t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
12558 {
12559 tree low_bound = TREE_PURPOSE (t);
12560 tree length = TREE_VALUE (t);
12561
12562 i--;
12563 if (low_bound
12564 && TREE_CODE (low_bound) == INTEGER_CST
12565 && TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (low_bound))
12566 > TYPE_PRECISION (sizetype))
12567 low_bound = fold_convert (sizetype, low_bound);
12568 if (length
12569 && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST
12570 && TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (length))
12571 > TYPE_PRECISION (sizetype))
12572 length = fold_convert (sizetype, length);
12573 if (low_bound == NULL_TREE)
12574 low_bound = integer_zero_node;
12575 if (!maybe_zero_len && i > first_non_one)
12576 {
12577 if (integer_nonzerop (low_bound))
12578 goto do_warn_noncontiguous;
12579 if (length != NULL_TREE
12580 && TREE_CODE (length) == INTEGER_CST
12581 && TYPE_DOMAIN (types[i])
12582 && TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (types[i]))
12583 && TREE_CODE (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (types[i])))
12584 == INTEGER_CST)
12585 {
12586 tree size;
12587 size = size_binop (PLUS_EXPR,
12588 TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (types[i])),
12589 size_one_node);
12590 if (!tree_int_cst_equal (length, size))
12591 {
12592 do_warn_noncontiguous:
12593 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12594 "array section is not contiguous in %qs "
12595 "clause",
12596 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12597 return true;
12598 }
12599 }
12600 if (length != NULL_TREE
12601 && TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (length))
12602 {
12603 if (side_effects == NULL_TREE)
12604 side_effects = length;
12605 else
12606 side_effects = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR,
12607 TREE_TYPE (side_effects),
12608 length, side_effects);
12609 }
12610 }
12611 else
12612 {
12613 tree l;
12614
12615 if (i > first_non_one
12616 && ((length && integer_nonzerop (length))
12617 || OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION))
12618 continue;
12619 if (length)
12620 l = fold_convert (sizetype, length);
12621 else
12622 {
12623 l = size_binop (PLUS_EXPR,
12624 TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (types[i])),
12625 size_one_node);
12626 l = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, l,
12627 fold_convert (sizetype, low_bound));
12628 }
12629 if (i > first_non_one)
12630 {
12631 l = fold_build2 (NE_EXPR, boolean_type_node, l,
12632 size_zero_node);
12633 if (condition == NULL_TREE)
12634 condition = l;
12635 else
12636 condition = fold_build2 (BIT_AND_EXPR, boolean_type_node,
12637 l, condition);
12638 }
12639 else if (size == NULL_TREE)
12640 {
12641 size = size_in_bytes (TREE_TYPE (types[i]));
12642 tree eltype = TREE_TYPE (types[num - 1]);
12643 while (TREE_CODE (eltype) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12644 eltype = TREE_TYPE (eltype);
12645 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12646 {
12647 if (integer_zerop (size)
12648 || integer_zerop (size_in_bytes (eltype)))
12649 {
12650 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12651 "zero length array section in %qs clause",
12652 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
12653 return error_mark_node;
12654 }
12655 size = size_binop (EXACT_DIV_EXPR, size,
12656 size_in_bytes (eltype));
12657 }
12658 size = size_binop (MULT_EXPR, size, l);
12659 if (condition)
12660 size = fold_build3 (COND_EXPR, sizetype, condition,
12661 size, size_zero_node);
12662 }
12663 else
12664 size = size_binop (MULT_EXPR, size, l);
12665 }
12666 }
12667 if (side_effects)
12668 size = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, sizetype, side_effects, size);
12669 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
12670 {
12671 size = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, size, size_one_node);
12672 size = c_fully_fold (size, false, NULL);
12673 tree index_type = build_index_type (size);
12674 tree eltype = TREE_TYPE (first);
12675 while (TREE_CODE (eltype) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12676 eltype = TREE_TYPE (eltype);
12677 tree type = build_array_type (eltype, index_type);
12678 tree ptype = build_pointer_type (eltype);
12679 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12680 t = build_fold_addr_expr (t);
12681 tree t2 = build_fold_addr_expr (first);
12682 t2 = fold_convert_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12683 ptrdiff_type_node, t2);
12684 t2 = fold_build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), MINUS_EXPR,
12685 ptrdiff_type_node, t2,
12686 fold_convert_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12687 ptrdiff_type_node, t));
12688 t2 = c_fully_fold (t2, false, NULL);
12689 if (tree_fits_shwi_p (t2))
12690 t = build2 (MEM_REF, type, t,
12691 build_int_cst (ptype, tree_to_shwi (t2)));
12692 else
12693 {
12694 t2 = fold_convert_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), sizetype, t2);
12695 t = build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), POINTER_PLUS_EXPR,
12696 TREE_TYPE (t), t, t2);
12697 t = build2 (MEM_REF, type, t, build_int_cst (ptype, 0));
12698 }
12699 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c) = t;
12700 return false;
12701 }
12702 first = c_fully_fold (first, false, NULL);
12703 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c) = first;
12704 if (size)
12705 size = c_fully_fold (size, false, NULL);
12706 OMP_CLAUSE_SIZE (c) = size;
12707 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_MAP
12708 || (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF
12709 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == ARRAY_TYPE))
12710 return false;
12711 gcc_assert (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c) != GOMP_MAP_FORCE_DEVICEPTR);
12712 if (ort == C_ORT_OMP || ort == C_ORT_ACC)
12713 switch (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c))
12714 {
12715 case GOMP_MAP_ALLOC:
12716 case GOMP_MAP_TO:
12717 case GOMP_MAP_FROM:
12718 case GOMP_MAP_TOFROM:
12719 case GOMP_MAP_ALWAYS_TO:
12720 case GOMP_MAP_ALWAYS_FROM:
12721 case GOMP_MAP_ALWAYS_TOFROM:
12722 case GOMP_MAP_RELEASE:
12723 case GOMP_MAP_DELETE:
12724 case GOMP_MAP_FORCE_TO:
12725 case GOMP_MAP_FORCE_FROM:
12726 case GOMP_MAP_FORCE_TOFROM:
12727 case GOMP_MAP_FORCE_PRESENT:
12728 OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_MAYBE_ZERO_LENGTH_ARRAY_SECTION (c) = 1;
12729 break;
12730 default:
12731 break;
12732 }
12733 tree c2 = build_omp_clause (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), OMP_CLAUSE_MAP);
12734 if (ort != C_ORT_OMP && ort != C_ORT_ACC)
12735 OMP_CLAUSE_SET_MAP_KIND (c2, GOMP_MAP_POINTER);
12736 else if (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF)
12737 OMP_CLAUSE_SET_MAP_KIND (c2, GOMP_MAP_ALWAYS_POINTER);
12738 else
12739 OMP_CLAUSE_SET_MAP_KIND (c2, GOMP_MAP_FIRSTPRIVATE_POINTER);
12740 if (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c2) != GOMP_MAP_FIRSTPRIVATE_POINTER
12741 && !c_mark_addressable (t))
12742 return false;
12743 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c2) = t;
12744 t = build_fold_addr_expr (first);
12745 t = fold_convert_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), ptrdiff_type_node, t);
12746 tree ptr = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c2);
12747 if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (ptr)))
12748 ptr = build_fold_addr_expr (ptr);
12749 t = fold_build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), MINUS_EXPR,
12750 ptrdiff_type_node, t,
12751 fold_convert_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12752 ptrdiff_type_node, ptr));
12753 t = c_fully_fold (t, false, NULL);
12754 OMP_CLAUSE_SIZE (c2) = t;
12755 OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c2) = OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
12756 OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c) = c2;
12757 }
12758 return false;
12759}
12760
12761/* Helper function of finish_omp_clauses. Clone STMT as if we were making
12762 an inline call. But, remap
12763 the OMP_DECL1 VAR_DECL (omp_out resp. omp_orig) to PLACEHOLDER
12764 and OMP_DECL2 VAR_DECL (omp_in resp. omp_priv) to DECL. */
12765
12766static tree
12767c_clone_omp_udr (tree stmt, tree omp_decl1, tree omp_decl2,
12768 tree decl, tree placeholder)
12769{
12770 copy_body_data id;
12771 hash_map<tree, tree> decl_map;
12772
12773 decl_map.put (omp_decl1, placeholder);
12774 decl_map.put (omp_decl2, decl);
12775 memset (&id, 0, sizeof (id));
12776 id.src_fn = DECL_CONTEXT (omp_decl1);
12777 id.dst_fn = current_function_decl;
12778 id.src_cfun = DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (id.src_fn);
12779 id.decl_map = &decl_map;
12780
12781 id.copy_decl = copy_decl_no_change;
12782 id.transform_call_graph_edges = CB_CGE_DUPLICATE;
12783 id.transform_new_cfg = true;
12784 id.transform_return_to_modify = false;
12785 id.transform_lang_insert_block = NULL;
12786 id.eh_lp_nr = 0;
12787 walk_tree (&stmt, copy_tree_body_r, &id, NULL);
12788 return stmt;
12789}
12790
12791/* Helper function of c_finish_omp_clauses, called via walk_tree.
12792 Find OMP_CLAUSE_PLACEHOLDER (passed in DATA) in *TP. */
12793
12794static tree
12795c_find_omp_placeholder_r (tree *tp, int *, void *data)
12796{
12797 if (*tp == (tree) data)
12798 return *tp;
12799 return NULL_TREE;
12800}
12801
12802/* For all elements of CLAUSES, validate them against their constraints.
12803 Remove any elements from the list that are invalid. */
12804
12805tree
12806c_finish_omp_clauses (tree clauses, enum c_omp_region_type ort)
12807{
12808 bitmap_head generic_head, firstprivate_head, lastprivate_head;
12809 bitmap_head aligned_head, map_head, map_field_head, oacc_reduction_head;
12810 tree c, t, type, *pc;
12811 tree simdlen = NULL_TREE, safelen = NULL_TREE;
12812 bool branch_seen = false;
12813 bool copyprivate_seen = false;
12814 bool linear_variable_step_check = false;
12815 tree *nowait_clause = NULL;
12816 bool ordered_seen = false;
12817 tree schedule_clause = NULL_TREE;
12818 bool oacc_async = false;
12819
12820 bitmap_obstack_initialize (NULL);
12821 bitmap_initialize (&generic_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12822 bitmap_initialize (&firstprivate_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12823 bitmap_initialize (&lastprivate_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12824 bitmap_initialize (&aligned_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12825 bitmap_initialize (&map_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12826 bitmap_initialize (&map_field_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12827 bitmap_initialize (&oacc_reduction_head, &bitmap_default_obstack);
12828
12829 if (ort & C_ORT_ACC)
12830 for (c = clauses; c; c = OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c))
12831 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_ASYNC)
12832 {
12833 oacc_async = true;
12834 break;
12835 }
12836
12837 for (pc = &clauses, c = clauses; c ; c = *pc)
12838 {
12839 bool remove = false;
12840 bool need_complete = false;
12841 bool need_implicitly_determined = false;
12842
12843 switch (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c))
12844 {
12845 case OMP_CLAUSE_SHARED:
12846 need_implicitly_determined = true;
12847 goto check_dup_generic;
12848
12849 case OMP_CLAUSE_PRIVATE:
12850 need_complete = true;
12851 need_implicitly_determined = true;
12852 goto check_dup_generic;
12853
12854 case OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION:
12855 need_implicitly_determined = true;
12856 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
12857 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST)
12858 {
12859 if (handle_omp_array_sections (c, ort))
12860 {
12861 remove = true;
12862 break;
12863 }
12864
12865 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
12866 }
12867 t = require_complete_type (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), t);
12868 if (t == error_mark_node)
12869 {
12870 remove = true;
12871 break;
12872 }
12873 if (oacc_async)
12874 c_mark_addressable (t);
12875 type = TREE_TYPE (t);
12876 if (TREE_CODE (t) == MEM_REF)
12877 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
12878 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12879 {
12880 tree oatype = type;
12881 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (t) != MEM_REF);
12882 while (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12883 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
12884 if (integer_zerop (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (type)))
12885 {
12886 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12887 "%qD in %<reduction%> clause is a zero size array",
12888 t);
12889 remove = true;
12890 break;
12891 }
12892 tree size = size_binop (EXACT_DIV_EXPR, TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (oatype),
12893 TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (type));
12894 if (integer_zerop (size))
12895 {
12896 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12897 "%qD in %<reduction%> clause is a zero size array",
12898 t);
12899 remove = true;
12900 break;
12901 }
12902 size = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, size, size_one_node);
12903 tree index_type = build_index_type (size);
12904 tree atype = build_array_type (type, index_type);
12905 tree ptype = build_pointer_type (type);
12906 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
12907 t = build_fold_addr_expr (t);
12908 t = build2 (MEM_REF, atype, t, build_int_cst (ptype, 0));
12909 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c) = t;
12910 }
12911 if (TYPE_ATOMIC (type))
12912 {
12913 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12914 "%<_Atomic%> %qE in %<reduction%> clause", t);
12915 remove = true;
12916 break;
12917 }
12918 if (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_PLACEHOLDER (c) == NULL_TREE
12919 && (FLOAT_TYPE_P (type)
12920 || TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE))
12921 {
12922 enum tree_code r_code = OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_CODE (c);
12923 const char *r_name = NULL;
12924
12925 switch (r_code)
12926 {
12927 case PLUS_EXPR:
12928 case MULT_EXPR:
12929 case MINUS_EXPR:
12930 break;
12931 case MIN_EXPR:
12932 if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
12933 r_name = "min";
12934 break;
12935 case MAX_EXPR:
12936 if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
12937 r_name = "max";
12938 break;
12939 case BIT_AND_EXPR:
12940 r_name = "&";
12941 break;
12942 case BIT_XOR_EXPR:
12943 r_name = "^";
12944 break;
12945 case BIT_IOR_EXPR:
12946 r_name = "|";
12947 break;
12948 case TRUTH_ANDIF_EXPR:
12949 if (FLOAT_TYPE_P (type))
12950 r_name = "&&";
12951 break;
12952 case TRUTH_ORIF_EXPR:
12953 if (FLOAT_TYPE_P (type))
12954 r_name = "||";
12955 break;
12956 default:
12957 gcc_unreachable ();
12958 }
12959 if (r_name)
12960 {
12961 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12962 "%qE has invalid type for %<reduction(%s)%>",
12963 t, r_name);
12964 remove = true;
12965 break;
12966 }
12967 }
12968 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_PLACEHOLDER (c) == error_mark_node)
12969 {
12970 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12971 "user defined reduction not found for %qE", t);
12972 remove = true;
12973 break;
12974 }
12975 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_PLACEHOLDER (c))
12976 {
12977 tree list = OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_PLACEHOLDER (c);
12978 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
12979 tree placeholder = build_decl (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12980 VAR_DECL, NULL_TREE, type);
12981 tree decl_placeholder = NULL_TREE;
12982 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_PLACEHOLDER (c) = placeholder;
12983 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (placeholder) = 1;
12984 DECL_IGNORED_P (placeholder) = 1;
12985 if (TREE_CODE (t) == MEM_REF)
12986 {
12987 decl_placeholder = build_decl (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
12988 VAR_DECL, NULL_TREE, type);
12989 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_DECL_PLACEHOLDER (c) = decl_placeholder;
12990 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl_placeholder) = 1;
12991 DECL_IGNORED_P (decl_placeholder) = 1;
12992 }
12993 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 0)))
12994 c_mark_addressable (placeholder);
12995 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 1)))
12996 c_mark_addressable (decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder
12997 : OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c));
12998 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_MERGE (c)
12999 = c_clone_omp_udr (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 2),
13000 TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 0),
13001 TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 1),
13002 decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder
13003 : OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c), placeholder);
13004 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_MERGE (c)
13005 = build3_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), BIND_EXPR,
13006 void_type_node, NULL_TREE,
13007 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_MERGE (c), NULL_TREE);
13008 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_MERGE (c)) = 1;
13009 if (TREE_VEC_LENGTH (list) == 6)
13010 {
13011 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 3)))
13012 c_mark_addressable (decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder
13013 : OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c));
13014 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 4)))
13015 c_mark_addressable (placeholder);
13016 tree init = TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 5);
13017 if (init == error_mark_node)
13018 init = DECL_INITIAL (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 3));
13019 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c)
13020 = c_clone_omp_udr (init, TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 4),
13021 TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 3),
13022 decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder
13023 : OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c), placeholder);
13024 if (TREE_VEC_ELT (list, 5) == error_mark_node)
13025 {
13026 tree v = decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder : t;
13027 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c)
13028 = build2 (INIT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (v), v,
13029 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c));
13030 }
13031 if (walk_tree (&OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c),
13032 c_find_omp_placeholder_r,
13033 placeholder, NULL))
13034 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_OMP_ORIG_REF (c) = 1;
13035 }
13036 else
13037 {
13038 tree init;
13039 tree v = decl_placeholder ? decl_placeholder : t;
13040 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (v)))
13041 init = build_constructor (TREE_TYPE (v), NULL);
13042 else
13043 init = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (v), integer_zero_node);
13044 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c)
13045 = build2 (INIT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (v), v, init);
13046 }
13047 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c)
13048 = build3_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), BIND_EXPR,
13049 void_type_node, NULL_TREE,
13050 OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c), NULL_TREE);
13051 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_INIT (c)) = 1;
13052 }
13053 if (TREE_CODE (t) == MEM_REF)
13054 {
13055 if (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (t))) == NULL_TREE
13056 || TREE_CODE (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (t))))
13057 != INTEGER_CST)
13058 {
13059 sorry ("variable length element type in array "
13060 "%<reduction%> clause");
13061 remove = true;
13062 break;
13063 }
13064 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13065 if (TREE_CODE (t) == POINTER_PLUS_EXPR)
13066 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13067 if (TREE_CODE (t) == ADDR_EXPR)
13068 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13069 }
13070 goto check_dup_generic_t;
13071
13072 case OMP_CLAUSE_COPYPRIVATE:
13073 copyprivate_seen = true;
13074 if (nowait_clause)
13075 {
13076 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (*nowait_clause),
13077 "%<nowait%> clause must not be used together "
13078 "with %<copyprivate%>");
13079 *nowait_clause = OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (*nowait_clause);
13080 nowait_clause = NULL;
13081 }
13082 goto check_dup_generic;
13083
13084 case OMP_CLAUSE_COPYIN:
13085 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13086 if (!VAR_P (t) || !DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (t))
13087 {
13088 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13089 "%qE must be %<threadprivate%> for %<copyin%>", t);
13090 remove = true;
13091 break;
13092 }
13093 goto check_dup_generic;
13094
13095 case OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR:
13096 if (ort != C_ORT_OMP_DECLARE_SIMD)
13097 need_implicitly_determined = true;
13098 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13099 if (ort != C_ORT_OMP_DECLARE_SIMD
13100 && OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_KIND (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_DEFAULT)
13101 {
13102 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13103 "modifier should not be specified in %<linear%> "
13104 "clause on %<simd%> or %<for%> constructs");
13105 OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_KIND (c) = OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_DEFAULT;
13106 }
13107 if (ort & C_ORT_CILK)
13108 {
13109 if (!INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (t))
13110 && !SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (t))
13111 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) != POINTER_TYPE)
13112 {
13113 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13114 "linear clause applied to non-integral, "
13115 "non-floating, non-pointer variable with type %qT",
13116 TREE_TYPE (t));
13117 remove = true;
13118 break;
13119 }
13120 }
13121 else
13122 {
13123 if (!INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (t))
13124 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) != POINTER_TYPE)
13125 {
13126 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13127 "linear clause applied to non-integral non-pointer "
13128 "variable with type %qT", TREE_TYPE (t));
13129 remove = true;
13130 break;
13131 }
13132 if (TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13133 {
13134 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13135 "%<_Atomic%> %qD in %<linear%> clause", t);
13136 remove = true;
13137 break;
13138 }
13139 }
13140 if (ort == C_ORT_OMP_DECLARE_SIMD)
13141 {
13142 tree s = OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c);
13143 if (TREE_CODE (s) == PARM_DECL)
13144 {
13145 OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_VARIABLE_STRIDE (c) = 1;
13146 /* map_head bitmap is used as uniform_head if
13147 declare_simd. */
13148 if (!bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (s)))
13149 linear_variable_step_check = true;
13150 goto check_dup_generic;
13151 }
13152 if (TREE_CODE (s) != INTEGER_CST)
13153 {
13154 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13155 "%<linear%> clause step %qE is neither constant "
13156 "nor a parameter", s);
13157 remove = true;
13158 break;
13159 }
13160 }
13161 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c))) == POINTER_TYPE)
13162 {
13163 tree s = OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c);
13164 s = pointer_int_sum (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), PLUS_EXPR,
13165 OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c), s);
13166 s = fold_build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), MINUS_EXPR,
13167 sizetype, fold_convert (sizetype, s),
13168 fold_convert
13169 (sizetype, OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c)));
13170 if (s == error_mark_node)
13171 s = size_one_node;
13172 OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c) = s;
13173 }
13174 else
13175 OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c)
13176 = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (t), OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c));
13177 goto check_dup_generic;
13178
13179 check_dup_generic:
13180 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13181 check_dup_generic_t:
13182 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13183 {
13184 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13185 "%qE is not a variable in clause %qs", t,
13186 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13187 remove = true;
13188 }
13189 else if (ort == C_ORT_ACC
13190 && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION)
13191 {
13192 if (bitmap_bit_p (&oacc_reduction_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13193 {
13194 error ("%qD appears more than once in reduction clauses", t);
13195 remove = true;
13196 }
13197 else
13198 bitmap_set_bit (&oacc_reduction_head, DECL_UID (t));
13199 }
13200 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t))
13201 || bitmap_bit_p (&firstprivate_head, DECL_UID (t))
13202 || bitmap_bit_p (&lastprivate_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13203 {
13204 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13205 "%qE appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13206 remove = true;
13207 }
13208 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_PRIVATE
13209 && bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13210 {
13211 if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13212 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13213 else
13214 error ("%qD appears both in data and map clauses", t);
13215 remove = true;
13216 }
13217 else
13218 bitmap_set_bit (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t));
13219 break;
13220
13221 case OMP_CLAUSE_FIRSTPRIVATE:
13222 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13223 need_complete = true;
13224 need_implicitly_determined = true;
13225 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13226 {
13227 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13228 "%qE is not a variable in clause %<firstprivate%>", t);
13229 remove = true;
13230 }
13231 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t))
13232 || bitmap_bit_p (&firstprivate_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13233 {
13234 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13235 "%qE appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13236 remove = true;
13237 }
13238 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13239 {
13240 if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13241 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13242 else
13243 error ("%qD appears both in data and map clauses", t);
13244 remove = true;
13245 }
13246 else
13247 bitmap_set_bit (&firstprivate_head, DECL_UID (t));
13248 break;
13249
13250 case OMP_CLAUSE_LASTPRIVATE:
13251 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13252 need_complete = true;
13253 need_implicitly_determined = true;
13254 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13255 {
13256 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13257 "%qE is not a variable in clause %<lastprivate%>", t);
13258 remove = true;
13259 }
13260 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t))
13261 || bitmap_bit_p (&lastprivate_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13262 {
13263 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13264 "%qE appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13265 remove = true;
13266 }
13267 else
13268 bitmap_set_bit (&lastprivate_head, DECL_UID (t));
13269 break;
13270
13271 case OMP_CLAUSE_ALIGNED:
13272 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13273 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13274 {
13275 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13276 "%qE is not a variable in %<aligned%> clause", t);
13277 remove = true;
13278 }
13279 else if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (t))
13280 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) != ARRAY_TYPE)
13281 {
13282 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13283 "%qE in %<aligned%> clause is neither a pointer nor "
13284 "an array", t);
13285 remove = true;
13286 }
13287 else if (TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13288 {
13289 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13290 "%<_Atomic%> %qD in %<aligned%> clause", t);
13291 remove = true;
13292 break;
13293 }
13294 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&aligned_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13295 {
13296 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13297 "%qE appears more than once in %<aligned%> clauses",
13298 t);
13299 remove = true;
13300 }
13301 else
13302 bitmap_set_bit (&aligned_head, DECL_UID (t));
13303 break;
13304
13305 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND:
13306 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13307 if (t == NULL_TREE)
13308 {
13309 gcc_assert (OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND_KIND (c)
13310 == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND_SOURCE);
13311 break;
13312 }
13313 if (OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND_KIND (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND_SINK)
13314 {
13315 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST);
13316 for (; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
13317 {
13318 tree decl = TREE_VALUE (t);
13319 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == POINTER_TYPE)
13320 {
13321 tree offset = TREE_PURPOSE (t);
13322 bool neg = wi::neg_p ((wide_int) offset);
13323 offset = fold_unary (ABS_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (offset), offset);
13324 tree t2 = pointer_int_sum (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13325 neg ? MINUS_EXPR : PLUS_EXPR,
13326 decl, offset);
13327 t2 = fold_build2_loc (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), MINUS_EXPR,
13328 sizetype,
13329 fold_convert (sizetype, t2),
13330 fold_convert (sizetype, decl));
13331 if (t2 == error_mark_node)
13332 {
13333 remove = true;
13334 break;
13335 }
13336 TREE_PURPOSE (t) = t2;
13337 }
13338 }
13339 break;
13340 }
13341 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST)
13342 {
13343 if (handle_omp_array_sections (c, ort))
13344 remove = true;
13345 break;
13346 }
13347 if (t == error_mark_node)
13348 remove = true;
13349 else if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13350 {
13351 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13352 "%qE is not a variable in %<depend%> clause", t);
13353 remove = true;
13354 }
13355 else if (!c_mark_addressable (t))
13356 remove = true;
13357 break;
13358
13359 case OMP_CLAUSE_MAP:
13360 case OMP_CLAUSE_TO:
13361 case OMP_CLAUSE_FROM:
13362 case OMP_CLAUSE__CACHE_:
13363 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13364 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST)
13365 {
13366 if (handle_omp_array_sections (c, ort))
13367 remove = true;
13368 else
13369 {
13370 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13371 if (!lang_hooks.types.omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13372 {
13373 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13374 "array section does not have mappable type "
13375 "in %qs clause",
13376 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13377 remove = true;
13378 }
13379 else if (TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13380 {
13381 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13382 "%<_Atomic%> %qE in %qs clause", t,
13383 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13384 remove = true;
13385 }
13386 while (TREE_CODE (t) == ARRAY_REF)
13387 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13388 if (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF
13389 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
13390 {
13391 while (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF)
13392 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13393 if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_field_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13394 break;
13395 if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13396 {
13397 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_MAP)
13398 error ("%qD appears more than once in motion"
13399 " clauses", t);
13400 else if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13401 error ("%qD appears more than once in data"
13402 " clauses", t);
13403 else
13404 error ("%qD appears more than once in map"
13405 " clauses", t);
13406 remove = true;
13407 }
13408 else
13409 {
13410 bitmap_set_bit (&map_head, DECL_UID (t));
13411 bitmap_set_bit (&map_field_head, DECL_UID (t));
13412 }
13413 }
13414 }
13415 break;
13416 }
13417 if (t == error_mark_node)
13418 {
13419 remove = true;
13420 break;
13421 }
13422 if (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF
13423 && (ort & C_ORT_OMP)
13424 && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE__CACHE_)
13425 {
13426 if (DECL_BIT_FIELD (TREE_OPERAND (t, 1)))
13427 {
13428 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13429 "bit-field %qE in %qs clause",
13430 t, omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13431 remove = true;
13432 }
13433 else if (!lang_hooks.types.omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13434 {
13435 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13436 "%qE does not have a mappable type in %qs clause",
13437 t, omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13438 remove = true;
13439 }
13440 else if (TYPE_ATOMIC (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13441 {
13442 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13443 "%<_Atomic%> %qE in %qs clause", t,
13444 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13445 remove = true;
13446 }
13447 while (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF)
13448 {
13449 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)))
13450 == UNION_TYPE)
13451 {
13452 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13453 "%qE is a member of a union", t);
13454 remove = true;
13455 break;
13456 }
13457 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
13458 }
13459 if (remove)
13460 break;
13461 if (VAR_P (t) || TREE_CODE (t) == PARM_DECL)
13462 {
13463 if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_field_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13464 break;
13465 }
13466 }
13467 if (!VAR_P (t) && TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13468 {
13469 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13470 "%qE is not a variable in %qs clause", t,
13471 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13472 remove = true;
13473 }
13474 else if (VAR_P (t) && DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (t))
13475 {
13476 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13477 "%qD is threadprivate variable in %qs clause", t,
13478 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13479 remove = true;
13480 }
13481 else if ((OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_MAP
13482 || (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c)
13483 != GOMP_MAP_FIRSTPRIVATE_POINTER))
13484 && !c_mark_addressable (t))
13485 remove = true;
13486 else if (!(OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_MAP
13487 && (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c) == GOMP_MAP_POINTER
13488 || (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c)
13489 == GOMP_MAP_FIRSTPRIVATE_POINTER)
13490 || (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c)
13491 == GOMP_MAP_FORCE_DEVICEPTR)))
13492 && t == OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c)
13493 && !lang_hooks.types.omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13494 {
13495 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13496 "%qD does not have a mappable type in %qs clause", t,
13497 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13498 remove = true;
13499 }
13500 else if (TREE_TYPE (t) == error_mark_node)
13501 remove = true;
13502 else if (TYPE_ATOMIC (strip_array_types (TREE_TYPE (t))))
13503 {
13504 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13505 "%<_Atomic%> %qE in %qs clause", t,
13506 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13507 remove = true;
13508 }
13509 else if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_MAP
13510 && OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND (c) == GOMP_MAP_FIRSTPRIVATE_POINTER)
13511 {
13512 if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t))
13513 || bitmap_bit_p (&firstprivate_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13514 {
13515 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13516 remove = true;
13517 }
13518 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13519 {
13520 if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13521 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13522 else
13523 error ("%qD appears both in data and map clauses", t);
13524 remove = true;
13525 }
13526 else
13527 bitmap_set_bit (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t));
13528 }
13529 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&map_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13530 {
13531 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_MAP)
13532 error ("%qD appears more than once in motion clauses", t);
13533 else if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13534 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13535 else
13536 error ("%qD appears more than once in map clauses", t);
13537 remove = true;
13538 }
13539 else if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t))
13540 || bitmap_bit_p (&firstprivate_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13541 {
13542 if (ort == C_ORT_ACC)
13543 error ("%qD appears more than once in data clauses", t);
13544 else
13545 error ("%qD appears both in data and map clauses", t);
13546 remove = true;
13547 }
13548 else
13549 {
13550 bitmap_set_bit (&map_head, DECL_UID (t));
13551 if (t != OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c)
13552 && TREE_CODE (OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c)) == COMPONENT_REF)
13553 bitmap_set_bit (&map_field_head, DECL_UID (t));
13554 }
13555 break;
13556
13557 case OMP_CLAUSE_TO_DECLARE:
13558 case OMP_CLAUSE_LINK:
13559 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13560 if (TREE_CODE (t) == FUNCTION_DECL
13561 && OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_TO_DECLARE)
13562 ;
13563 else if (!VAR_P (t))
13564 {
13565 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_TO_DECLARE)
13566 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13567 "%qE is neither a variable nor a function name in "
13568 "clause %qs", t,
13569 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13570 else
13571 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13572 "%qE is not a variable in clause %qs", t,
13573 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13574 remove = true;
13575 }
13576 else if (DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (t))
13577 {
13578 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13579 "%qD is threadprivate variable in %qs clause", t,
13580 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13581 remove = true;
13582 }
13583 else if (!lang_hooks.types.omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (t)))
13584 {
13585 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13586 "%qD does not have a mappable type in %qs clause", t,
13587 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13588 remove = true;
13589 }
13590 if (remove)
13591 break;
13592 if (bitmap_bit_p (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t)))
13593 {
13594 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13595 "%qE appears more than once on the same "
13596 "%<declare target%> directive", t);
13597 remove = true;
13598 }
13599 else
13600 bitmap_set_bit (&generic_head, DECL_UID (t));
13601 break;
13602
13603 case OMP_CLAUSE_UNIFORM:
13604 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13605 if (TREE_CODE (t) != PARM_DECL)
13606 {
13607 if (DECL_P (t))
13608 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13609 "%qD is not an argument in %<uniform%> clause", t);
13610 else
13611 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13612 "%qE is not an argument in %<uniform%> clause", t);
13613 remove = true;
13614 break;
13615 }
13616 /* map_head bitmap is used as uniform_head if declare_simd. */
13617 bitmap_set_bit (&map_head, DECL_UID (t));
13618 goto check_dup_generic;
13619
13620 case OMP_CLAUSE_IS_DEVICE_PTR:
13621 case OMP_CLAUSE_USE_DEVICE_PTR:
13622 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13623 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) != POINTER_TYPE
13624 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (t)) != ARRAY_TYPE)
13625 {
13626 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13627 "%qs variable is neither a pointer nor an array",
13628 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13629 remove = true;
13630 }
13631 goto check_dup_generic;
13632
13633 case OMP_CLAUSE_NOWAIT:
13634 if (copyprivate_seen)
13635 {
13636 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13637 "%<nowait%> clause must not be used together "
13638 "with %<copyprivate%>");
13639 remove = true;
13640 break;
13641 }
13642 nowait_clause = pc;
13643 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13644 continue;
13645
13646 case OMP_CLAUSE_IF:
13647 case OMP_CLAUSE_NUM_THREADS:
13648 case OMP_CLAUSE_NUM_TEAMS:
13649 case OMP_CLAUSE_THREAD_LIMIT:
13650 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEFAULT:
13651 case OMP_CLAUSE_UNTIED:
13652 case OMP_CLAUSE_COLLAPSE:
13653 case OMP_CLAUSE_FINAL:
13654 case OMP_CLAUSE_MERGEABLE:
13655 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEVICE:
13656 case OMP_CLAUSE_DIST_SCHEDULE:
13657 case OMP_CLAUSE_PARALLEL:
13658 case OMP_CLAUSE_FOR:
13659 case OMP_CLAUSE_SECTIONS:
13660 case OMP_CLAUSE_TASKGROUP:
13661 case OMP_CLAUSE_PROC_BIND:
13662 case OMP_CLAUSE_PRIORITY:
13663 case OMP_CLAUSE_GRAINSIZE:
13664 case OMP_CLAUSE_NUM_TASKS:
13665 case OMP_CLAUSE_NOGROUP:
13666 case OMP_CLAUSE_THREADS:
13667 case OMP_CLAUSE_SIMD:
13668 case OMP_CLAUSE_HINT:
13669 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEFAULTMAP:
13670 case OMP_CLAUSE__CILK_FOR_COUNT_:
13671 case OMP_CLAUSE_NUM_GANGS:
13672 case OMP_CLAUSE_NUM_WORKERS:
13673 case OMP_CLAUSE_VECTOR_LENGTH:
13674 case OMP_CLAUSE_ASYNC:
13675 case OMP_CLAUSE_WAIT:
13676 case OMP_CLAUSE_AUTO:
13677 case OMP_CLAUSE_INDEPENDENT:
13678 case OMP_CLAUSE_SEQ:
13679 case OMP_CLAUSE_GANG:
13680 case OMP_CLAUSE_WORKER:
13681 case OMP_CLAUSE_VECTOR:
13682 case OMP_CLAUSE_TILE:
13683 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13684 continue;
13685
13686 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE:
13687 if (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (c) & OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_NONMONOTONIC)
13688 {
13689 const char *p = NULL;
13690 switch (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (c) & OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_MASK)
13691 {
13692 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_STATIC: p = "static"; break;
13693 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_DYNAMIC: break;
13694 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_GUIDED: break;
13695 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_AUTO: p = "auto"; break;
13696 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_RUNTIME: p = "runtime"; break;
13697 default: gcc_unreachable ();
13698 }
13699 if (p)
13700 {
13701 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13702 "%<nonmonotonic%> modifier specified for %qs "
13703 "schedule kind", p);
13704 OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (c)
13705 = (enum omp_clause_schedule_kind)
13706 (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (c)
13707 & ~OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_NONMONOTONIC);
13708 }
13709 }
13710 schedule_clause = c;
13711 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13712 continue;
13713
13714 case OMP_CLAUSE_ORDERED:
13715 ordered_seen = true;
13716 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13717 continue;
13718
13719 case OMP_CLAUSE_SAFELEN:
13720 safelen = c;
13721 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13722 continue;
13723 case OMP_CLAUSE_SIMDLEN:
13724 simdlen = c;
13725 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13726 continue;
13727
13728 case OMP_CLAUSE_INBRANCH:
13729 case OMP_CLAUSE_NOTINBRANCH:
13730 if (branch_seen)
13731 {
13732 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13733 "%<inbranch%> clause is incompatible with "
13734 "%<notinbranch%>");
13735 remove = true;
13736 break;
13737 }
13738 branch_seen = true;
13739 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13740 continue;
13741
13742 default:
13743 gcc_unreachable ();
13744 }
13745
13746 if (!remove)
13747 {
13748 t = OMP_CLAUSE_DECL (c);
13749
13750 if (need_complete)
13751 {
13752 t = require_complete_type (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c), t);
13753 if (t == error_mark_node)
13754 remove = true;
13755 }
13756
13757 if (need_implicitly_determined)
13758 {
13759 const char *share_name = NULL;
13760
13761 if (VAR_P (t) && DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (t))
13762 share_name = "threadprivate";
13763 else if (TREE_READONLY (t))
13764 {
13765 /* const vars may be specified in firstprivate clause. */
13766 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) != OMP_CLAUSE_FIRSTPRIVATE)
13767 share_name = "shared";
13768 }
13769 if (share_name)
13770 {
13771 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13772 "%qE is predetermined %qs for %qs",
13773 t, share_name,
13774 omp_clause_code_name[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c)]);
13775 remove = true;
13776 }
13777 }
13778 }
13779
13780 if (remove)
13781 *pc = OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13782 else
13783 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13784 }
13785
13786 if (simdlen
13787 && safelen
13788 && tree_int_cst_lt (OMP_CLAUSE_SAFELEN_EXPR (safelen),
13789 OMP_CLAUSE_SIMDLEN_EXPR (simdlen)))
13790 {
13791 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (simdlen),
13792 "%<simdlen%> clause value is bigger than "
13793 "%<safelen%> clause value");
13794 OMP_CLAUSE_SIMDLEN_EXPR (simdlen)
13795 = OMP_CLAUSE_SAFELEN_EXPR (safelen);
13796 }
13797
13798 if (ordered_seen
13799 && schedule_clause
13800 && (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (schedule_clause)
13801 & OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_NONMONOTONIC))
13802 {
13803 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (schedule_clause),
13804 "%<nonmonotonic%> schedule modifier specified together "
13805 "with %<ordered%> clause");
13806 OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (schedule_clause)
13807 = (enum omp_clause_schedule_kind)
13808 (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND (schedule_clause)
13809 & ~OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_NONMONOTONIC);
13810 }
13811
13812 if (linear_variable_step_check)
13813 for (pc = &clauses, c = clauses; c ; c = *pc)
13814 {
13815 bool remove = false;
13816 if (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (c) == OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR
13817 && OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_VARIABLE_STRIDE (c)
13818 && !bitmap_bit_p (&map_head,
13819 DECL_UID (OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c))))
13820 {
13821 error_at (OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (c),
13822 "%<linear%> clause step is a parameter %qD not "
13823 "specified in %<uniform%> clause",
13824 OMP_CLAUSE_LINEAR_STEP (c));
13825 remove = true;
13826 }
13827
13828 if (remove)
13829 *pc = OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13830 else
13831 pc = &OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (c);
13832 }
13833
13834 bitmap_obstack_release (NULL);
13835 return clauses;
13836}
13837
13838/* Return code to initialize DST with a copy constructor from SRC.
13839 C doesn't have copy constructors nor assignment operators, only for
13840 _Atomic vars we need to perform __atomic_load from src into a temporary
13841 followed by __atomic_store of the temporary to dst. */
13842
13843tree
13844c_omp_clause_copy_ctor (tree clause, tree dst, tree src)
13845{
13846 if (!really_atomic_lvalue (dst) && !really_atomic_lvalue (src))
13847 return build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (dst), dst, src);
13848
13849 location_t loc = OMP_CLAUSE_LOCATION (clause);
13850 tree type = TREE_TYPE (dst);
13851 tree nonatomic_type = build_qualified_type (type, TYPE_UNQUALIFIED);
13852 tree tmp = create_tmp_var (nonatomic_type);
13853 tree tmp_addr = build_fold_addr_expr (tmp);
13854 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (tmp) = 1;
13855 TREE_NO_WARNING (tmp) = 1;
13856 tree src_addr = build_fold_addr_expr (src);
13857 tree dst_addr = build_fold_addr_expr (dst);
13858 tree seq_cst = build_int_cst (integer_type_node, MEMMODEL_SEQ_CST);
13859 vec<tree, va_gc> *params;
13860 /* Expansion of a generic atomic load may require an addition
13861 element, so allocate enough to prevent a resize. */
13862 vec_alloc (params, 4);
13863
13864 /* Build __atomic_load (&src, &tmp, SEQ_CST); */
13865 tree fndecl = builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD);
13866 params->quick_push (src_addr);
13867 params->quick_push (tmp_addr);
13868 params->quick_push (seq_cst);
13869 tree load = c_build_function_call_vec (loc, vNULL, fndecl, params, NULL);
13870
13871 vec_alloc (params, 4);
13872
13873 /* Build __atomic_store (&dst, &tmp, SEQ_CST); */
13874 fndecl = builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_STORE);
13875 params->quick_push (dst_addr);
13876 params->quick_push (tmp_addr);
13877 params->quick_push (seq_cst);
13878 tree store = c_build_function_call_vec (loc, vNULL, fndecl, params, NULL);
13879 return build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, void_type_node, load, store);
13880}
13881
13882/* Create a transaction node. */
13883
13884tree
13885c_finish_transaction (location_t loc, tree block, int flags)
13886{
13887 tree stmt = build_stmt (loc, TRANSACTION_EXPR, block);
13888 if (flags & TM_STMT_ATTR_OUTER)
13889 TRANSACTION_EXPR_OUTER (stmt) = 1;
13890 if (flags & TM_STMT_ATTR_RELAXED)
13891 TRANSACTION_EXPR_RELAXED (stmt) = 1;
13892 return add_stmt (stmt);
13893}
13894
13895/* Make a variant type in the proper way for C/C++, propagating qualifiers
13896 down to the element type of an array. If ORIG_QUAL_TYPE is not
13897 NULL, then it should be used as the qualified type
13898 ORIG_QUAL_INDIRECT levels down in array type derivation (to
13899 preserve information about the typedef name from which an array
13900 type was derived). */
13901
13902tree
13903c_build_qualified_type (tree type, int type_quals, tree orig_qual_type,
13904 size_t orig_qual_indirect)
13905{
13906 if (type == error_mark_node)
13907 return type;
13908
13909 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
13910 {
13911 tree t;
13912 tree element_type = c_build_qualified_type (TREE_TYPE (type),
13913 type_quals, orig_qual_type,
13914 orig_qual_indirect - 1);
13915
13916 /* See if we already have an identically qualified type. */
13917 if (orig_qual_type && orig_qual_indirect == 0)
13918 t = orig_qual_type;
13919 else
13920 for (t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type); t; t = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t))
13921 {
13922 if (TYPE_QUALS (strip_array_types (t)) == type_quals
13923 && TYPE_NAME (t) == TYPE_NAME (type)
13924 && TYPE_CONTEXT (t) == TYPE_CONTEXT (type)
13925 && attribute_list_equal (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t),
13926 TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (type)))
13927 break;
13928 }
13929 if (!t)
13930 {
13931 tree domain = TYPE_DOMAIN (type);
13932
13933 t = build_variant_type_copy (type);
13934 TREE_TYPE (t) = element_type;
13935
13936 if (TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY_P (element_type)
13937 || (domain && TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY_P (domain)))
13938 SET_TYPE_STRUCTURAL_EQUALITY (t);
13939 else if (TYPE_CANONICAL (element_type) != element_type
13940 || (domain && TYPE_CANONICAL (domain) != domain))
13941 {
13942 tree unqualified_canon
13943 = build_array_type (TYPE_CANONICAL (element_type),
13944 domain? TYPE_CANONICAL (domain)
13945 : NULL_TREE);
13946 if (TYPE_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER (type))
13947 {
13948 unqualified_canon
13949 = build_distinct_type_copy (unqualified_canon);
13950 TYPE_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER (unqualified_canon) = 1;
13951 }
13952 TYPE_CANONICAL (t)
13953 = c_build_qualified_type (unqualified_canon, type_quals);
13954 }
13955 else
13956 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = t;
13957 }
13958 return t;
13959 }
13960
13961 /* A restrict-qualified pointer type must be a pointer to object or
13962 incomplete type. Note that the use of POINTER_TYPE_P also allows
13963 REFERENCE_TYPEs, which is appropriate for C++. */
13964 if ((type_quals & TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT)
13965 && (!POINTER_TYPE_P (type)
13966 || !C_TYPE_OBJECT_OR_INCOMPLETE_P (TREE_TYPE (type))))
13967 {
13968 error ("invalid use of %<restrict%>");
13969 type_quals &= ~TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT;
13970 }
13971
13972 tree var_type = (orig_qual_type && orig_qual_indirect == 0
13973 ? orig_qual_type
13974 : build_qualified_type (type, type_quals));
13975 /* A variant type does not inherit the list of incomplete vars from the
13976 type main variant. */
13977 if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (var_type)
13978 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (var_type) != var_type)
13979 C_TYPE_INCOMPLETE_VARS (var_type) = 0;
13980 return var_type;
13981}
13982
13983/* Build a VA_ARG_EXPR for the C parser. */
13984
13985tree
13986c_build_va_arg (location_t loc1, tree expr, location_t loc2, tree type)
13987{
13988 if (error_operand_p (type))
13989 return error_mark_node;
13990 /* VA_ARG_EXPR cannot be used for a scalar va_list with reverse storage
13991 order because it takes the address of the expression. */
13992 else if (handled_component_p (expr)
13993 && reverse_storage_order_for_component_p (expr))
13994 {
13995 error_at (loc1, "cannot use %<va_arg%> with reverse storage order");
13996 return error_mark_node;
13997 }
13998 else if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
13999 {
14000 error_at (loc2, "second argument to %<va_arg%> is of incomplete "
14001 "type %qT", type);
14002 return error_mark_node;
14003 }
14004 else if (warn_cxx_compat && TREE_CODE (type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
14005 warning_at (loc2, OPT_Wc___compat,
14006 "C++ requires promoted type, not enum type, in %<va_arg%>");
14007 return build_va_arg (loc2, expr, type);
14008}
14009
14010/* Return truthvalue of whether T1 is the same tree structure as T2.
14011 Return 1 if they are the same. Return 0 if they are different. */
14012
14013bool
14014c_tree_equal (tree t1, tree t2)
14015{
14016 enum tree_code code1, code2;
14017
14018 if (t1 == t2)
14019 return true;
14020 if (!t1 || !t2)
14021 return false;
14022
14023 for (code1 = TREE_CODE (t1);
14024 CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (code1)
14025 || code1 == NON_LVALUE_EXPR;
14026 code1 = TREE_CODE (t1))
14027 t1 = TREE_OPERAND (t1, 0);
14028 for (code2 = TREE_CODE (t2);
14029 CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (code2)
14030 || code2 == NON_LVALUE_EXPR;
14031 code2 = TREE_CODE (t2))
14032 t2 = TREE_OPERAND (t2, 0);
14033
14034 /* They might have become equal now. */
14035 if (t1 == t2)
14036 return true;
14037
14038 if (code1 != code2)
14039 return false;
14040
14041 switch (code1)
14042 {
14043 case INTEGER_CST:
14044 return wi::eq_p (t1, t2);
14045
14046 case REAL_CST:
14047 return real_equal (&TREE_REAL_CST (t1), &TREE_REAL_CST (t2));
14048
14049 case STRING_CST:
14050 return TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t1) == TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t2)
14051 && !memcmp (TREE_STRING_POINTER (t1), TREE_STRING_POINTER (t2),
14052 TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t1));
14053
14054 case FIXED_CST:
14055 return FIXED_VALUES_IDENTICAL (TREE_FIXED_CST (t1),
14056 TREE_FIXED_CST (t2));
14057
14058 case COMPLEX_CST:
14059 return c_tree_equal (TREE_REALPART (t1), TREE_REALPART (t2))
14060 && c_tree_equal (TREE_IMAGPART (t1), TREE_IMAGPART (t2));
14061
14062 case VECTOR_CST:
14063 return operand_equal_p (t1, t2, OEP_ONLY_CONST);
14064
14065 case CONSTRUCTOR:
14066 /* We need to do this when determining whether or not two
14067 non-type pointer to member function template arguments
14068 are the same. */
14069 if (!comptypes (TREE_TYPE (t1), TREE_TYPE (t2))
14070 || CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (t1) != CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (t2))
14071 return false;
14072 {
14073 tree field, value;
14074 unsigned int i;
14075 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (t1), i, field, value)
14076 {
14077 constructor_elt *elt2 = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (t2, i);
14078 if (!c_tree_equal (field, elt2->index)
14079 || !c_tree_equal (value, elt2->value))
14080 return false;
14081 }
14082 }
14083 return true;
14084
14085 case TREE_LIST:
14086 if (!c_tree_equal (TREE_PURPOSE (t1), TREE_PURPOSE (t2)))
14087 return false;
14088 if (!c_tree_equal (TREE_VALUE (t1), TREE_VALUE (t2)))
14089 return false;
14090 return c_tree_equal (TREE_CHAIN (t1), TREE_CHAIN (t2));
14091
14092 case SAVE_EXPR:
14093 return c_tree_equal (TREE_OPERAND (t1, 0), TREE_OPERAND (t2, 0));
14094
14095 case CALL_EXPR:
14096 {
14097 tree arg1, arg2;
14098 call_expr_arg_iterator iter1, iter2;
14099 if (!c_tree_equal (CALL_EXPR_FN (t1), CALL_EXPR_FN (t2)))
14100 return false;
14101 for (arg1 = first_call_expr_arg (t1, &iter1),
14102 arg2 = first_call_expr_arg (t2, &iter2);
14103 arg1 && arg2;
14104 arg1 = next_call_expr_arg (&iter1),
14105 arg2 = next_call_expr_arg (&iter2))
14106 if (!c_tree_equal (arg1, arg2))
14107 return false;
14108 if (arg1 || arg2)
14109 return false;
14110 return true;
14111 }
14112
14113 case TARGET_EXPR:
14114 {
14115 tree o1 = TREE_OPERAND (t1, 0);
14116 tree o2 = TREE_OPERAND (t2, 0);
14117
14118 /* Special case: if either target is an unallocated VAR_DECL,
14119 it means that it's going to be unified with whatever the
14120 TARGET_EXPR is really supposed to initialize, so treat it
14121 as being equivalent to anything. */
14122 if (VAR_P (o1) && DECL_NAME (o1) == NULL_TREE
14123 && !DECL_RTL_SET_P (o1))
14124 /*Nop*/;
14125 else if (VAR_P (o2) && DECL_NAME (o2) == NULL_TREE
14126 && !DECL_RTL_SET_P (o2))
14127 /*Nop*/;
14128 else if (!c_tree_equal (o1, o2))
14129 return false;
14130
14131 return c_tree_equal (TREE_OPERAND (t1, 1), TREE_OPERAND (t2, 1));
14132 }
14133
14134 case COMPONENT_REF:
14135 if (TREE_OPERAND (t1, 1) != TREE_OPERAND (t2, 1))
14136 return false;
14137 return c_tree_equal (TREE_OPERAND (t1, 0), TREE_OPERAND (t2, 0));
14138
14139 case PARM_DECL:
14140 case VAR_DECL:
14141 case CONST_DECL:
14142 case FIELD_DECL:
14143 case FUNCTION_DECL:
14144 case IDENTIFIER_NODE:
14145 case SSA_NAME:
14146 return false;
14147
14148 case TREE_VEC:
14149 {
14150 unsigned ix;
14151 if (TREE_VEC_LENGTH (t1) != TREE_VEC_LENGTH (t2))
14152 return false;
14153 for (ix = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (t1); ix--;)
14154 if (!c_tree_equal (TREE_VEC_ELT (t1, ix),
14155 TREE_VEC_ELT (t2, ix)))
14156 return false;
14157 return true;
14158 }
14159
14160 default:
14161 break;
14162 }
14163
14164 switch (TREE_CODE_CLASS (code1))
14165 {
14166 case tcc_unary:
14167 case tcc_binary:
14168 case tcc_comparison:
14169 case tcc_expression:
14170 case tcc_vl_exp:
14171 case tcc_reference:
14172 case tcc_statement:
14173 {
14174 int i, n = TREE_OPERAND_LENGTH (t1);
14175
14176 switch (code1)
14177 {
14178 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
14179 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
14180 case POSTINCREMENT_EXPR:
14181 case POSTDECREMENT_EXPR:
14182 n = 1;
14183 break;
14184 case ARRAY_REF:
14185 n = 2;
14186 break;
14187 default:
14188 break;
14189 }
14190
14191 if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (code1) == tcc_vl_exp
14192 && n != TREE_OPERAND_LENGTH (t2))
14193 return false;
14194
14195 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
14196 if (!c_tree_equal (TREE_OPERAND (t1, i), TREE_OPERAND (t2, i)))
14197 return false;
14198
14199 return true;
14200 }
14201
14202 case tcc_type:
14203 return comptypes (t1, t2);
14204 default:
14205 gcc_unreachable ();
14206 }
14207 /* We can get here with --disable-checking. */
14208 return false;
14209}
14210
14211/* Inserts "cleanup" functions after the function-body of FNDECL. FNDECL is a
14212 spawn-helper and BODY is the newly created body for FNDECL. */
14213
14214void
14215cilk_install_body_with_frame_cleanup (tree fndecl, tree body, void *w)
14216{
14217 tree list = alloc_stmt_list ();
14218 tree frame = make_cilk_frame (fndecl);
14219 tree dtor = create_cilk_function_exit (frame, false, true);
14220 add_local_decl (cfun, frame);
14221
14222 DECL_SAVED_TREE (fndecl) = list;
14223 tree frame_ptr = build1 (ADDR_EXPR, build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (frame)),
14224 frame);
14225 tree body_list = cilk_install_body_pedigree_operations (frame_ptr);
14226 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (body_list) == STATEMENT_LIST);
14227
14228 tree detach_expr = build_call_expr (cilk_detach_fndecl, 1, frame_ptr);
14229 append_to_statement_list (detach_expr, &body_list);
14230
14231 cilk_outline (fndecl, &body, (struct wrapper_data *) w);
14232 body = fold_build_cleanup_point_expr (void_type_node, body);
14233
14234 append_to_statement_list (body, &body_list);
14235 append_to_statement_list (build_stmt (EXPR_LOCATION (body), TRY_FINALLY_EXPR,
14236 body_list, dtor), &list);
14237}
14238
14239/* Returns true when the function declaration FNDECL is implicit,
14240 introduced as a result of a call to an otherwise undeclared
14241 function, and false otherwise. */
14242
14243bool
14244c_decl_implicit (const_tree fndecl)
14245{
14246 return C_DECL_IMPLICIT (fndecl);
14247}
